Basically the Moon Presence, by granting you it's powers, it's enabled you to become one. You have the blood of one, the womb of one, and the mind/knowledge of one, and the power of one, which allows you to be reborn as one. When you fight the Moon Presence, you are not really human at that point anymore. If it weren't for the Moon Presence, you would've gone insane, became a beast, or became something like Rom, Ebrietas, Celestial Emissary, Living Failures, or those little baby things in Upper Cathedral Ward crawling around, which Ebrietas is really just a fully matured version of.
TL:DR Moon Presence unintentionally An Hero's by granting hunters his blessing to do whatever (which is assumingly, defeating the last remaining bits of another old one (Mergo)), however this unintentionally allowed the Hunter to succeed in becoming an Old One.

posts.author: Anonymous
posts.text:
>>399221261
Your character is the only succesful attempt at making an Old God.
Really when it came down to it there were several ingredients to it. The Blood was the most common, but it turned people into beasts, but Marked Hunters were immune.
The second involved trying to birth one. We see many failed attempts at birthing an old one. Orphan of Kos and Mergo just straight up died, they died before birth. Orphan died because Kos died, and Mergo was a bunch of idiots using a human body as a surrogate womb. You succeed because you have a full umbilical cord of a Old One
The last one of the most important. In Lovecraftian shit, humanity is completely beneath Elder Gods. We are not powerful enough to make things greater than them, and the knowledge drives us insane. We cannot hope to be powerful as them, and any attempts are doomed to failure. All the countless kin we see are this, even Mergo (even though TECHNICALLY not kin, reminder it's the baby, not the thing you fight, that is the old one), failures. Humanity cannot become greater, or kill an old one. Then in Bloodborne, the only ones immune to this, are the Hunter, Eileen, Djura, and Gerhman. They didn't succumb to the plague of beasts, they didn't go insane, they were immortal when they were marked by the hunter's mark. They were all marked, all of them. You could maybe argue others, but they were the only ones we know to be marked. Marked by an Old One. An Old One grants them these powers. The Moon Presence if you don't have the umbilical cords makes you his servant forever, as what Gerhman was, if you defeat Gerhman, because you cannot stand up against the Moon Presence. However by being marked, you have the Blood of an Old One without succumbing to beasthood, you have knowledge of an old one without going insane, and you have the womb or body or something of Old Ones in the form of the Umbilical Cord, allowing you to be properly reborn as one.
CONT

posts.author: Thomas Evans (noreply@blogger.com)
posts.title: Ousmane Dembele returns to training nearly 3 months after surgery
posts.text: Ousmane Dembele trained with his Barcelona teammates for the first time since rupturing a thigh tendon nearly three months ago. Dembele, the most expensive signing in Barcelona’s history, joined the rest of the group for the first part of Wednesday’s session and then continued with his recovery routine. The 20-year-old Dembele hurt his left leg in the team’s 2-1 win at Getafe on Sept. 16. It was one of his first matches since being signed from Borussia Dortmund in a deal that could potentially reach nearly 150 million euros ($177 million). Dembele underwent surgery in Finland three days after getting injured. The club said at the time that he was expected to be sidelined for about four months. Barcelona has not given a new timetable on Dembele’s return. The club leads the Spanish league with 36 points, five more than Valencia.

posts.author: DVNCI3
posts.title: Am I stuck with this gmail forever?
posts.text:
Someone was using my computer and went to check if an email address was available. They went to gmail.com and it brought up this page https://accounts.google.com/b/0/AddMailService because I was already signed into my google account (that did not have a gmail account associated with it) on that computer. They entered the email they were looking to possibly create, thinking it was the place you go to to create a new gmail but instead they attached that gmail address to my google account!
I have since followed the directions on how to revert to my other (non gmail) email associated with the account by deleting the newly created gmail from my google account but now I have no option to create a gmail for this google account.. Something that I had planned on doing in the future.. It tells my that this other gmail address can't be changed.. Which sucks because that address has nothing to do with me whatsoever.. I know that there's a bunch of arrows pointing to this mistake address forever being associated with my long-standing google account, but is there ANY possible way to assign a different gmail address to this google account or remove the association from the mistake one?

thread.title: Experiences putting regular gas in Sport/Sport Touring Models?
thread.title_full: Experiences putting regular gas in Sport/Sport Touring Models? | 2016+ Honda Civic Forum (10th Gen) - Type R Forum, Si Forum - CivicX.com

posts.author: xRiCeBoYx
posts.text:
Did an experiment recently while on a road trip (Vegas to northern Cali and back on I-5) and testing out 87 vs 91 octane in my '18 sport hatch cvt. With 87 octane and cruise set at 85mph, noticed lack of power and the cruise control accelerated to maintain speed far more often. Average mpg didn't go above 34 for that tank. With the tank of 91 octane, cruise also set to 85mph, the cruise control didn't have to open up the throttle as much and average mpg didn't drop below 36.5.
Road conditions for both tanks I observed were fairly constant -- flat-ish with little variance in road grade.
